	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=32254><span id= >Nixoh</span></a><br><span id=notbold>484 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.40]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>All of the &quot;aura of [heath/healing/courage/bravery/etc]&quot; stack with eachother and with all other forms of HP regen.<br><br>That is to say, this is effectively flowing thought for hitpoints.<br><br>However, that's not why this is a great effect.<br><br>For those who don't know: the way you get better taunt is to raise your ATK and DEX (assuming you have a proccing weapon(s) with good taunt-value) and lower your delay (directly via weapon or indirectly via haste).<br><br>You can max out haste and DEX easily (chanter buffs can max DEX without breaking a sweat), though the quest for a good taunting weapon is always fun.<br><br>You can max out your STR fairly easily and that helps ATK.<br><br>However, to get raw ATK out of an item is a godsend to those who need to eek out that last bit from their weapons. There's nothing like missing less to up your dps (which, for an MT is really just for taunt value, you're not going to touch the nukers).<br><br>Anyone who has hard information to the contrary (not just, &quot;ATK ain't worth doodoo&quot;) please speak up.<br><br>[edited: changed &quot;mana regen&quot; to &quot;hp regen&quot;, oops]<br><br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Wed Sep 17 15:28:16 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br><span class=sm>----------------------------</span><br>You gain experience!<br>The Goblin Warlord hits YOU for 50 points!<br></td></tr>
